Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.75,0:00:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah God has the purpose \Nof gathering His people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.69,0:00:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,out of Satan’s world \Ninto His congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.13,0:00:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ Jesus promised us \Nthat he would be with us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.03,0:00:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,until the conclusion \Nof this system of things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.77,0:00:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,When we see \Nthis huge organization worldwide, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.01,0:00:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,we know that Jesus \Nis fulfilling his promise \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.14,0:00:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jehovah is executing \NHis purposes in a wonderful way. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.08,0:00:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This huge organization \Nhas many services \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.99,0:00:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,or ministries \Nassociated with it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.72,0:00:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It can only be accomplished \Nby means of Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.39,0:00:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He is the orchestrator \Nof this organization.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.47,0:00:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle Paul, \Nhere in 1 Corinthians chapter 12, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.64,0:00:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,explains in great detail \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.07,0:01:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,how Jehovah \Norganizes His organization. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.71,0:01:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If we’d look at verse 14 \Nof 1 Corinthians chapter 12, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.68,0:01:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it says: \N“Indeed, the body is made up \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.32,0:01:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,not of one member \Nbut of many.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.62,0:01:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So Paul is using the body, \Nthe human body, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.29,0:01:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,as an analogy \Nof the organization. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.20,0:01:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And it has many members. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.20,0:01:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Each individual member \Nis assigned a ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.17,0:01:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us read here \Nverses 4 through 6. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.28,0:01:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: \N“Now there are different gifts, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.68,0:01:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“but there is the same spirit; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.05,0:01:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“and there are different ministries, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.65,0:01:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“and yet there is the same Lord; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.45,0:01:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“and there are different activities, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.79,0:01:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“and yet it is the same God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.66,0:01:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,who performs them all in everyone.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.23,0:01:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This reminds us that this organization \Ndoes not belong to any man. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.04,0:02:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,No human is putting it together; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.91,0:02:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,no human is moving it along. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.24,0:02:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It is Jehovah God himself.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.24,0:02:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And we are helped \Nby Paul in this chapter \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.35,0:02:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand \Nour relationship to one another. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.32,0:02:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us read here \Nverses 17 and 19 and 21. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.32,0:02:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It says, \N1 Corinthians 12:17: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.53,0:02:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“If the whole body were an eye, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.03,0:02:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“where would the sense of hearing be? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.90,0:02:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If it were all hearing, \Nwhere would the sense of smell be?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.67,0:02:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Nineteen: \N“If they were all the same member, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.68,0:02:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,where would the body be?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.88,0:02:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And 21: \N“The eye cannot say to the hand, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.08,0:02:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘I do not need you,’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.08,0:02:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“or again, \Nthe head cannot say to the feet, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.92,0:02:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I do not need you.’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.92,0:02:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We all understand \Nwe need each other. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.83,0:02:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We do different operations \Nor ministries, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.16,0:03:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but we need each other \Nvery much. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.57,0:03:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s why it says \Nin verse 20: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.04,0:03:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“Now they are many members, \Nyet one body.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.94,0:03:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We are still one body. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.04,0:03:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We belong to the same congregation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.05,0:03:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this brings us \Nto the text for today in verse 22 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.62,0:03:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,where Paul says: \N“On the contrary, the members of the body \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.22,0:03:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that seem to be weaker are necessary.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.29,0:03:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So “weaker” in this context, \Nwhat does it mean? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.53,0:03:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It does not refer \Nthat this member is deficient \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.70,0:03:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,or not able \Nto do their work; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.87,0:03:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,no, it just means \Nthat this member may be, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.60,0:03:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,from a physical point of view, \Nseem weaker.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.94,0:03:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we have an older brother \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.71,0:03:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,suffering with some illness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.31,0:03:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and he cannot do \Nas much as he used to do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.32,0:03:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it mean that \Nhe is not fulfilling his assignment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.65,0:03:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,or that he does not fit \Ninto God’s arrangement \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.22,0:04:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,or that he \Nis useless to Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.22,0:04:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.63,0:04:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He may seem to be weaker, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.40,0:04:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but we understand \Nhow that works, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.77,0:04:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and we appreciate \NGod’s arrangement. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.07,0:04:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Look what it says in verse 23: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.14,0:04:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“And the parts of the body \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.14,0:04:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“that we think to be less honorable \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.71,0:04:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“we surround with greater honor, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.71,0:04:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“so our unseemly parts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.85,0:04:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,are treated with greater modesty.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.32,0:04:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is God’s arrangement. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.32,0:04:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 24 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.15,0:04:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“Whereas our attractive parts \Ndo not need anything. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.56,0:04:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“Nevertheless, \NGod has so composed the body, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.56,0:04:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,giving greater honor \Nto the part that had a lack.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.13,0:04:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So there is no division \Nin the body. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.04,0:04:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It cooperates. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.04,0:04:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You do not have members \Nlooking down on others \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.01,0:04:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,because of their inability \Nor limited circumstances. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.75,0:05:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why it says in verse 25: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.12,0:05:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“So that there should be \Nno division in the body, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.89,0:05:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but its members should have \Nmutual concern for one another.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.20,0:05:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,How does this work? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.20,0:05:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,How has Jehovah arranged \Nand orchestrated this organization? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.87,0:05:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s beautifully described by Paul \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.57,0:05:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in Ephesians 4:16. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.14,0:05:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now in verse 15 here in Ephesians 4, \NPaul says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.75,0:05:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“Let us by love grow up in all things \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.49,0:05:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,into him who is the head, Christ.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.12,0:05:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ Jesus is the Head. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.46,0:05:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no pyramid structure. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.03,0:05:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ said: \N“Your Leader is one.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.73,0:05:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it says, from verse 16, \Nthe first part of verse 16, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.70,0:05:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,it explains how Jehovah God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.91,0:05:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,organizes his people. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.44,0:06:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: \N“From him,” from Christ, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.91,0:06:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“all the body \Nis harmoniously joined together \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.92,0:06:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“and made to cooperate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.18,0:06:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,through every joint \Nthat gives what is needed.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.59,0:06:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So it is harmoniously joined together. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.43,0:06:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s like the human hand. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.43,0:06:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The fingers are joined by the palm. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.33,0:06:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The palm is joined to the wrist. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.63,0:06:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a harmonious joining together, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.60,0:06:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it says here, \Nthey are made to cooperate. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.41,0:06:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So they have been designed \Nto fit together, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.41,0:06:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to cooperate, \Nto work together. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.48,0:06:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what Jehovah God does. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.88,0:06:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But then the second part of the verse \Nshows what we need to do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.68,0:06:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It says we need to give what is needed \Nand then it says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.92,0:06:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“When each respective member \Nfunctions properly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.79,0:06:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“this contributes \Nto the growth of the body \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.56,0:06:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,as it builds itself up in love.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.33,0:07:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is our function\N—to give what is needed, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.60,0:07:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to do what is required.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.27,0:07:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus illustrated that \Nso beautifully for us in John 13. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.68,0:07:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember the time when \Nhe washed the feet of the disciples. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.68,0:07:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We turn there to John 13, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.19,0:07:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and if we look \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.26,0:07:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,at verses 12 through 15, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.99,0:07:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus explained what he did. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.03,0:07:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he explains the purpose of this. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.30,0:07:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: \N“When, now, he had washed their feet \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.47,0:07:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“and had put \Nhis outer garments on, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.64,0:07:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“he again reclined at the table \Nand said to them: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.81,0:07:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Do you understand \Nwhat I have done to you? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.31,0:07:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘You address me \Nas “Teacher” and “Lord,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.65,0:07:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and you are correct, \Nfor I am such. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.09,0:07:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Therefore, if I, the Lord and Teacher, \Nwashed your feet, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.76,0:07:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘you also should wash \Nthe feet of one another. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.23,0:07:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘For I set the pattern for you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.63,0:08:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that just as I did to you, \Nyou should also do.’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.53,0:08:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So imagine, here is Jesus, \Nthe Head of the congregation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.91,0:08:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,he got down on his knees \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.97,0:08:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and washed the feet of his disciples, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.04,0:08:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and then he said \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.18,0:08:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we must follow that example.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.15,0:08:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what is the purpose \Nof this arrangement? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.82,0:08:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Each of us fits \Ninto God’s arrangement. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.99,0:08:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,All of us have a function, \Na beautiful function, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.16,0:08:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that is to serve one another\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.33,0:08:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,—give what is needed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.73,0:08:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,As stated there in Ephesians \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.64,0:08:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,in the final part of verse 16, \Nas we read: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.94,0:08:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“This contributes \Nto the growth of the body \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.78,0:08:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,as it builds itself up in love.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.15,0:08:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jehovah has made \Nthis wonderful arrangement \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.32,0:08:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of gathering his people together. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.75,0:09:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He will take this organization, \Nthis congregation of people, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.26,0:09:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,through into \Nthe righteous new system of things \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.83,0:09:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,where we will experience \Nwonderful blessings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.43,0:09:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But right now, \Nit is our opportunity to cooperate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.24,0:09:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and to work together \Nin love and unity. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.61,0:09:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And that way, \Nwhether we are weaker or stronger \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.01,0:09:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,from a physical point of view \Ndoes not matter, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.91,0:09:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re all part of the same body.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.99,0:00:05.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは目的を持って人々を—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.52,0:00:10.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,サタンの世から\N会衆へと集めてこられました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.70,0:00:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスも 事物の体制の終結の時まで\N共にいると約束しておられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.34,0:00:22.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,この巨大な世界的組織を見る時—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.31,0:00:26.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスがその約束を\N守っておられること そして—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.61,0:00:28.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが素晴らしい仕方で\Nご自分の目的を—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.95,0:00:32.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,果たしておられることが分かります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.78,0:00:40.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,この巨大な組織には\N様々な奉仕の分野があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.06,0:00:44.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,このようなことができるのは\Nエホバだけです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.66,0:00:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがこの組織を\N編成しておられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.93,0:00:53.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,使徒パウロは\Nコリント第一 12章で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.84,0:01:00.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの組織の仕方について\N詳しく述べています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.84,0:01:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,12章14節にはこうあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.22,0:01:13.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,“実際 体は一つの肢体ではなく\N 多くの肢体です” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.62,0:01:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここでパウロは 組織の類似として\N人体を用いています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.36,0:01:24.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,人体には たくさんの部位があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.43,0:01:29.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,それぞれの部位には\Nそれぞれの役割があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.41,0:01:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,12章4から6節を読みましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.08,0:01:39.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,“さて 賜物はさまざまですが\N 霊は同じです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.78,0:01:44.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,“奉仕の務めはさまざまでも\N 主は同じです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.75,0:01:46.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,“働きはさまざまでも—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.79,0:01:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“すべての人の中で\N あらゆる働きをされる神は同じです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.63,0:01:59.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから この組織は\N人間の組織ではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.30,0:02:04.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間が組織しているのでも\N人間が動かしているのでもありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.71,0:02:07.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがそうしておられるのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.41,0:02:13.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,同じ章でパウロは\Nわたしたち互いの関係について述べます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.98,0:02:18.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,17, 19, 21節を読みましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.45,0:02:21.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,コリント第一 12章です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.26,0:02:27.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,17節 “もし全身が目であったなら\N聴覚はどこなのですか”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.66,0:02:32.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“それが聴くことばかりであったなら\N においをかぐことはどこなのですか”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.17,0:02:35.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,19節—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.00,0:02:40.91,Default2,,0,0,0,, “もしそのすべてが一つの肢体であったなら\N 体はどこにあるのでしょうか”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.91,0:02:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,21節 “目は手に向かって「わたしに\Nあなたは必要でない」とは言えず—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.12,0:02:53.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,“頭も足に向かって「わたしにあなた方は\N 必要でない」とは言えません”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.59,0:02:57.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは互いを必要としている\Nということです \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.23,0:03:02.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,働きや任務はさまざまでも\N互いを大いに必要としているのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.90,0:03:07.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 20節には “しかし今\Nそれは多くの肢体であり—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.57,0:03:11.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,“それでもなお一つの体です”\N とあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.64,0:03:13.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは 一つの体—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.31,0:03:16.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,一つの会衆に属しているのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.15,0:03:21.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして今日の聖句 22節です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.22,0:03:24.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,“それどころか 実際には 体の中で—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.49,0:03:29.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ほかより弱く見える肢体が\N かえって必要なのであり” とあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.76,0:03:32.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここでいう “弱い” とは\Nどう意味でしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.80,0:03:35.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,その “弱い” 人が\N能力不足であるとか—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.83,0:03:38.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,用をなさないという意味ではなく—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.74,0:03:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,身体的に弱く見えるということです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.11,0:03:49.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,病気に苦しむ年配の兄弟は\N若いときほど働けないでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.88,0:03:52.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,だからといって\N割り当てを果たせないとか—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.75,0:03:55.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の組織の中に居場所がないとか—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.85,0:04:00.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバにとって役立たず ということでは\N決してありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.56,0:04:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,弱く見える人がいても\N組織は機能します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.00,0:04:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それが神の組織の素晴らしさです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.27,0:04:12.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,23節にはこうあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.54,0:04:16.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,“また 体の中で\N ほかより誉れが少ないと思える部分—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.81,0:04:20.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,“これをわたしたちは\N より豊かな誉れをもって包みます”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.84,0:04:23.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,“こうしてわたしたちの\N 見栄えのしない部分に—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.55,0:04:26.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,“他より豊かな麗しさが\N 添えられ[ます]”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.75,0:04:29.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,これが神の組織です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.45,0:04:35.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,24節 “一方 麗しい部分は\N何も必要としません”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.02,0:04:39.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,“しかしそうではあっても\N 神が体を組み立てたのであり—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.36,0:04:45.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“欠けたところのある部分に誉れを\N より豊かに与えて[おられます]”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.97,0:04:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから 体の各部は分裂することなく\N協働しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.38,0:04:55.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,他の部位が自分のように\N動かないからと言って— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.24,0:04:58.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,見下げることはしません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.22,0:05:02.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,25節にある通りです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.65,0:05:05.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,“体に分裂がないように—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.19,0:05:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“その肢体が互いに対して\N 同じ気づかいを示すようにされました”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.93,0:05:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはこの組織をどのように\N機能させておられるのでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.57,0:05:26.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,エフェソス 4章16節のパウロの言葉に\N美しく表現されています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.34,0:05:30.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず15節には こうあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.51,0:05:32.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,“すべての事において—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.45,0:05:37.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,“頭であるキリストを目ざして\N 成長してゆきましょう”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.22,0:05:39.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,頭はキリストです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.52,0:05:42.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,ピラミッド型組織ではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.33,0:05:47.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,“指導者は一人” と\N キリストは言われました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.70,0:05:49.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして16節の前半で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.87,0:05:54.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの組織の仕方について\Nこう説明されています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.87,0:05:58.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,“このキリストをもととして\N 体の各部すべては—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.04,0:06:00.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,“調和よく\N 組み合わされることにより—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.94,0:06:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“また必要なものを与える\N すべての関節を通して協働する” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.35,0:06:09.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,各部は調和し つながっています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.29,0:06:11.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,人の手のようです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.89,0:06:14.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,指は手のひらにつながり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.22,0:06:17.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,手のひらは手首につながっています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.56,0:06:23.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,調和よくつながり\Nここで言われているように 協働します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.13,0:06:29.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,つながり 協力し 一緒に働くように\Nデザインされているのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.21,0:06:33.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはそのように組織されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.68,0:06:38.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし わたしたちにも\N行うべきことがあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.21,0:06:45.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,16節は 必要とされているものを\N与えるようにと述べてから こう続きます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.72,0:06:49.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,“それぞれの部分が定めの機能を\N 果たすにつれて—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.29,0:06:56.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,“愛のうちに自らを築き上げることを\N 目ざした体の成長に資するのです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.93,0:06:58.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから 与えること—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.73,0:07:03.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,求められることを行なうことが\Nわたしたちの役目なのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.74,0:07:07.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスはそれを見事に実践されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.98,0:07:12.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨハネ 13章の\N弟子たちの足を洗った記録です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.38,0:07:16.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨハネ 13章12から15節を\Nお開きください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.62,0:07:20.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここでイエスは\Nご自分がなさったことの意味と—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.02,0:07:24.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを行なった理由を説明されます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.09,0:07:27.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,“さて 彼らの足を洗い\N 外衣を身に着け—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.93,0:07:33.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,“再び食卓について身を横にしてから\N イエスは彼らに言われた”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.67,0:07:36.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,“「わたしがあなた方にしたことが\N 分かりますか？”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.81,0:07:41.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなた方はわたしを\N『師』また『主』と呼びます”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.68,0:07:46.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,“そう言うのは正しいことです\N わたしはそのような者だからです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.88,0:07:53.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,“それで わたしが 主また師でありながら\N あなた方の足を洗ったのであれば—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.86,0:07:57.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなた方も互いに\N 足を洗い合うべきです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.43,0:08:00.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしはあなた方のために\N 模範を示しました”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.73,0:08:06.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなた方も わたしがあなた方にしたと\N 同じようにするためです」”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.00,0:08:09.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,想像してみてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.14,0:08:14.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆の頭イエスが 膝をついて\N弟子の足を洗われたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.84,0:08:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そしてその手本に倣うようにと\Nおっしゃいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.52,0:08:25.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,互いに仕え合う その目的は\N何でしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.45,0:08:29.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちすべてに\N役割があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.16,0:08:32.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはとても美しい役割です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.66,0:08:38.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,互いに仕え合い 必要とされているものを\N与えるという役割です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.97,0:08:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,先ほど読んだエフェソス 4章16節の\N最後にある通りです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.91,0:08:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“愛のうちに自らを築き上げることを\N 目ざした体の成長に資するのです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.15,0:08:55.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがこのような仕方で\N人々を組織されるのは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.08,0:08:57.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,実に素晴らしいことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.85,0:09:00.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは\Nこの組織 この会衆を—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.06,0:09:04.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,義の行き渡る新しい世に\N導き入れられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.09,0:09:07.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこでは\N素晴らしい祝福が待っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.83,0:09:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし今でも \N愛と一致を保ちながら協力し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.00,0:09:15.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,共に働くことができるのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.10,0:09:19.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうするなら 身体的に強いか弱いかに\Nかかわりなく—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.38,0:09:21.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,一つの体として\N結び合わされていることになるでしょう\N
